name: Aditi Indian Dining
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Rebecca Hester', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103560650888971860839/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu1x1dMH14FTqhSmyIK_SKGlnW4G2sduRy-hcbVP=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Hands down the best Indian food I have ever eaten. We will definitely be back next time we're in town.", 'time': 1645661066, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Amanda (WhatsDaHype)', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114962659501785236705/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8E3Hlyrlu-v9V72RcEmmKomw1yMHj33UQg3kHu=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'I was happy to find this restaurant wasn’t too far from me and parking isn’t a big hassle. There are several parking areas to choose from. The restaurant is small. I would suggest making reservations to ensure you get seated promptly in the evening. Service was a little slow so when we got our waiters attention we made sure to give our full order at one time. We tried the samosas which were good. Fresh, hot and flavorful. We also had chicken tikka masala and salmon tikka masala. The meats were tender but the sauce was sweet to me. I’m use to a balance of sweet and spicy. It wasn’t terrible but unexpected. The naan was fresh made and melted in my mouth. I preferred the regular naan over the cheese naan. The cheese didn’t add to my experience and was tasteless.', 'time': 1661006428, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Vincent Watson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111701775234433504294/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu2CRuhpL9sIRUo-1u2clhwN6qBsRBdbJH20IDFY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Excellent Indian fare in Kingstowne Center may be found here.

Vegetarian options are available, as are alcoholic beverages.

Butter chicken was outstanding!', 'time': 1657276123, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Meg Marquez-Ascher', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109165217044198124699/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_S3VD1z0xbayD1a4h2GUUhHV7r4pNnzDCa50oGB-g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': "Super good!!! We first came here for dinner and had an awesome experience then so we decided to try their lunch buffet. Food was just amazing! For people who aren't familiar with the cuisine (like me), the buffet gives you a chance to try various Indian dishes so you'll know what to order next time. Price is also reasonable at $18 including tax. The buffer had about 6 dishes, 2 varieties of rice, 2 dessert dishes, a few appetizers. I think single orders are between 10 to 18 bucks. So you're better to try the buffet! It's available Wednesday to Sunday from 12(?) to 230. Servers were just really, very nice! We plan to come back here with the whole family soon! If you haven't tried this place yet or thinking about trying, please do!!! I highly recommend! Worth your time, money, and calories!!! One thing I would say, I felt like the tables were too close to each other but doesn't take away from our wonderful experience!!!", 'time': 1664768319, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Stephen Hester', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109430630517736993179/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-iYzPE0oGfR6zh017QW97bLU63HePKPGLREgdRpA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'I was introduced to Aditi by a friend while here on business. After three visits within a week, I have decided that the food is awesome. My wife came to visit while I was here and she fell in love with the place. While I could live off the spinach chaat, the Chicken Tikka has become a favorite. The service has been fantastic and Sidnny gave us first-class attention. For someone who has never been a big fan of Indian cuisine, I can’t say enough about Aditi. We will definitely be back!', 'time': 1645658120, 'translated': False}]

name: Chili's Grill & Bar
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Gary Connor', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107659866968861861282/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9U_xvSUnIEa2BPttVtIKmN8GMHTXo28btqyQlL1NE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Friday lunch visit. Plenty of parking, no crowd. Traffic heavy. Easy to see from the road. Immediately seated. Eclectic American menu. A lot of interesting lunch combos. Soups came immediately and were hot and tasty. Sandwiches came shortly after. Very nice sandwiches. Tasty. Large.\nTotally enjoyed lunch.', 'time': 1645290468, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Nikk McAndrews', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107334019361773672219/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-1sbUtVj4BiOkGSQmljHcmqSamqqR-fmy3uWqeww=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "This Chili's location was great! I was visiting from Manassas and decided to stop in. Same great for, same great atmosphere. This location has a very good feel to it, with the warning rays of sun setting a good mood coming thru the front doors. The only gripes I could come up with were that the table was a bit dirty, and that the area from the parking lot to the inside has a door but it wasn't the front door....?? This is a apparently a mobile order To-Go door. It really throws off the look of the restaurant when the first door that guests can walk up to isn't the front door... But, I guess there's nothing the restaurant staff or managers can do about that, haha! That's an architect and engineer's thing. Overall the service was great. I ordered the chicken enchilada soup to start (no tortilla strips), and original chicken crispers as a main. They were both cooked well, and perfect. My server continually checked in on me and wasn't the talkative type. He let me say what I needed and left it simple, which I appreciated very much. He brought me a couple things when I asked for them and was always there to help at the right time. What I did find odd was that the person bringing me my food was not the person checking on me or taking my order. All in all, a great ending to the day for me. Thanks Chili's crew!", 'time': 1655666067, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Ivey Bedsole', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102768928661258663575/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3n5TKC29foCLIbPM8JKpraxX6rDc3ZRi2ZYF0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Ordered classic nachos with beef and thought I got nothing—there were mor hidden under aluminum foil! [{'author_name': 'Samone Jones', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104527591845300065792/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-y2DwIfU_IJkeYHNwZ8NaniiAROdNQDHExMe57UA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Some of the best Thai in the area! I had the Drunken Noodles with chicken mildly spicy. There is plenty of parking, it’s in a shopping area across the street from a movie theatre and beside an ice cream shop. Great location. I spent about $19 including tip which is standard for this area.

The food came out quickly. It was delicious. Their mildly spicy was fire 🔥 for me - I downed three glasses of water but it was still very delicious LOL! But you know spicy is relative. I highly recommend. I’ve had their pad Thai too and it was very good as well. Very authentic.', 'time': 1641407487, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': "Lyn'ay B", 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105767442488111137680/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu1zLiUcUotnhGpGhoqm0JZvG0XS1lbIWPLTOlyP=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Let me start by stating that the food is fresh, hot, and flavorful. Now we all know that the cost of meat and veggies has increased because of the plandemic 🙄but not RICE. They are out here charging dinner prices with appetizer portions. When I order a lunch meal I expected that. I expect my food to come in a black bottom plastic storage container not the container that holds my soup. I am very disappointed with a lunch carryout order that cost $52.44 with a tip from this establishment. name: Osteria Marzano
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Rachael Long', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104289176774737977314/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9-DtxxX3Q0ngDpi1byovY3--pTFyLpRwIlwhDCqw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'We found this place by chance when we were looking for somewhere to have a fake Valentine’s Day dinner near Springfield Town Center. The food was so good I couldn’t stop eating it. It was also incredibly affordable for how good it was. We will definitely be making this a regular place to eat for special occasions.

Don’t be deterred by the location. We thought we had the wrong address but it is actually on the ground floor of an office building on a side road by the medical center. We parked in the parking garage of the office building and walked around. I thought it was a little sketchy but the place was very nice on the inside.', 'time': 1645668219, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Nicole Manuel', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104886811955076706494/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9gbjuxGlc33SFLwFyVOXKvnVDHXAHefWycEghCy-w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'We have been before and it was better last time. name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
address: 5955 Kingstowne Towne Ctr, Ste 160, Alexandria, VA 22315, USA
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Weekend Warrior', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114630705948522558151/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8HbZWWTtKmCL_TaapBePO9wh06WXrytXVdQXve3A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "This Chipotle didn't have guacamole, or take NFC payments. I get that supply chain issues can effect the ingredients shortage, but there needs to be a sign that says what this restaurant is taking and not taking, has in stock or doesn't have in stock before beginning an order. No excuse for not having NFC payments.", 'time': 1641814442, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'justin morris', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103590181370480516660/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0bTPt38XxeSG4P6ADYEq6yPzFQ0gelDgFIrEpy=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'The employees here are very rude. It was our first time to eat here. The store at 5955 Kingstown T.C. #160 Alexandria, VA 22315. My mother in law ordered her food and asked for the salsa that is the mildest on the side…. They gave her the most spicy kind. She put a little on her food,  but it was all  to spicy so she couldn’t eat it at  all. She went back up to see if they would remake it since that is their mistake. They would not remake it and told her she had to go to the end of the line which was backed up to the door. They would not fix it at all and made it VERY clear to us that THEY DO NOT MAKE MISTAKES!!! I would like to know how to be so perfect that you never make a single mistake! She even offered to pay for a new one, and they said she had to go to the end of the line! Customer services should be your number one priority! With out customers you wouldn’t have a business period! If I could leave 0 stars or even negative stars I would! All they had to do is remake it and everything could have been just fine! But I guess taking 2 minutes to make it was to much trouble!
It took them longer to argue with us then it would have been to just fix their mistake! It was our first time to eat there and it will be our last and we were a group of 8!', 'time': 1650736608, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Victoria Lusk', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107356506099935232460/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_wZBzhnkgeJE5t8us6U8HAdpBib45VSxhruHvysQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': "Admittedly, I eat at Chipotle 2-3x a week. The fresh, healthy, high protein ingredients make Chipotle a great choice for a quick and tasty post-workout meal. Unfortunately, this location doesn't meet the bar Chipotle has set for its customers. I'm not sure when things changed. My workplace is close to this location so prior to COVID, I often ordered from this location. While I worked from home, I ate at the Burke and Woodbridge location, both are consistent with the Chipotle brand I've grown to love. Now, I'm back in the office after two years, and the Kingstowne location is not the same. The staff, mostly the women there, aren't very hospitable. They are impatient and lack customer service skills. I think training in this particular area would be beneficial. And, as crazy as this sounds coming from someone like me who adds salt to my food before I even try it, THE FOOD IS EXTREMELY SALTY.  Someone in the kitchen has a very heavy hand. Two weeks ago, I couldn't finish my burrito after TWO bites. I was literally choking on salt. The salt was so overpowering, I couldn't even taste the food. I didn't complain, though. I chalked it up as a bad day in kitchen. But again today, the food is so salty that I can't enjoy my meal. I'm on the fence about returning my food but twice in a row, I paid for a meal I cannot eat. Honestly, I'm not one for negative reviews. If I really don't like a place or service, I'd rather just not return. However, my hope is that management will see this and work towards correcting these issues. Either way, I'm still a Chipotle fan, just not this particular location.", 'time': 1652722066, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Darren Lee', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109009666644282177799/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-jR1azL3De55zmeLZonbWrBRvs2gbtJv4VGE4fJA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'This is the worst Chipotle I’ve ever been to. I live 5 minutes away, so I’ve frequented it way more than I’d have liked to. What’s most impressive is their sheer consistency in providing bad service and screwing up orders. The last 5 times in a row I went there they messed multiple things up. They ALWAYS forget drinks for kids meals or give the wrong ones, they serve extremely stale chips, and they have no clue how to roll burritos. I think I’ve had one burrito out of about 10 from them that didn’t just completely fall apart. They’re also terrible at managing mobile orders. They have a whole shelving system with letters for names set up for mobile orders, yet for some unfathomable reason, they keep all of the orders behind the register so you have to wait for 5-10 minutes until they acknowledge you to ask if your food is ready. Most of the time your order won’t be ready even though the “order ready” time has passed. They’ll even set it all out to make, but then just continue making food for the people in line - even though you’re standing right there and already told them you’re there to pick up your order. I don’t think this chipotle has ever gotten one of my orders completely correct. It’s almost like they train their employees to be bad at their jobs. I have to think the only reason this store is still in operation is because of its proximity to so many people and lack of another good option nearby. This place needs a complete overhaul in management and probably employees.', 'time': 1658601609, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'J Evins', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108344568069393651061/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu1etcuZM4SlNzg7K9G4dRy8lCwKz5OtohDDUn5d=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'Staff is very unfriendly/hostile.  Although close to me, I will be going to other locations from now on.

My first run in was when I attempted to get catered food for a party.  When I got the order home, I realized I only got 1/3 of it.  I called the restaurant, the manager kept insisting that I did not order the other items, even though I re-iterated that I had a receipt that said otherwise.  Eventually, after about 5 minutes of back and forth, I get an "oh here it is".  I sent my friend to pick up the additional items, since I was fuming at this point.

Yesterday, I ordered pickup.  My order was supposed to be ready at 7:50pm.  I arrived several minutes  after this -- the store does not use the self-serve pickup shelves, so  you have to ask for it at the register.  Anyway there was a line of  several people -- the checker was very unfriendly.  I told him my name  several times and even spelled it out.  Eventually, he gave me an order  -- the name wasn't even close.  I told him my name again, he then  threatened not to help me because I yelled my name.  Finally, about  8:15, he checked again -- my order was there the whole time -- it was  missing the large chips though.  Anyway, the fact that they do not use  the self-service shelves and the staff is very unfriendly, I will not be  going to this restaurant again.  Hopefully one of the others in the  area will be better.', 'time': 1650123772, 'translated': False}]

name: Stone Hot Pizza
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Iram S', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110181042298835843069/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-cCYhuRlm7c8Ed73sqjegqTVgky32Af6rjgnd9fg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'This location has changed so much in quality.
I remember when I used to come here - I could get fresh food and my correct order 99% of the time and in the few times there was an issue it was no big deal because the former person, Dia, would make sure it wouldn’t happen again.

Now, I’m lucky if I actually get fresh salad. The struggle with ordering their chicken Caesar salad is they don’t include chicken sometimes, sometimes no croutons and sometimes just old disgusting salad - visibly old. This is the 3rd time…unsure why they have something on their menu they don’t actually have the full ingredients for?! It’s a simple salad…never understood when it became so complicated?!

Ordered that along with a pizza today - it takes skill to burn the crusts of a pizza and still have the dough slightly undercooked. I scraped that off and put back in an oven. Obviously something is wrong…but no one is taking the time to check the quality.

Seems like the quality of the food in general has gone down aside from my issues with their food - a couple of months ago my friend and I went to order food and he was not happy with his order because originally giving him the wrong order then telling him they didn’t have it, then finally giving him a burnt version of his order.

Wish they could get it together. It is as if they truly don’t want your business. Quality inspection of the food people are paying for and consuming  would go a long way - apologies are empty words without action. Increasing the prices and decreasing the quality doesn’t make sense.', 'time': 1652641616, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Crystal C', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113991272595585015010/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu28cABCu1INUg5-DwAjA4_CG8YLKwxgR4MPXtG4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "Ordered a Napoli pizza on wheat crust with added chicken. name: Spin Pollo Kingstowne
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'MkMG09', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112325526165128906532/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_JWsjaEk4sbnJREL_g768YNbO9L79BrumOvYvGuQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "- food was fresh and had really good flavor, chicken was tinder and perfectly seasoned. The mashed potatoes were really good only wish I had asked for extra gravy, and the Mac and cheese was nice and cheesey.

- green sauce was just a little spicy with a nice cucumber taste. Yellow sauce taste like a paprika and mayonnaise type of sauce and the white one taste almost like a ranch with different spices. All really good.

- staff were friendly.

- service was quick considering how busy they were. Staff did seem a bit disorganized a little with a few orders But all got fixed.

- place was clean and organized.

- seating is a bit limited depending how busy they are.

- plenty of parking in this area.

- prices not too bad but you do get a decent amount of food for the price.

- they even sell popsicles.

- overall a good first experience and I'd recommend this location.", 'time': 1657479833, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'John Whyman', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111464731612208346940/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8WpwpDtqTjOwzNJAM88hpKD7n9l-WntJux1wrFTA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'Very good.  Had the quarter chicken with fries and coleslaw.   Very tasty.  I did ask my fies be cooked extra well done but that request was ignored after being told they would cook the fries well.  Also no refillable fountain drinks.  Recommended.  I will come back and try other options. Four falst food stars.', 'time': 1650490950, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Vincent Meli', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104795192564595938671/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0tQyfVavhzxCQd08zM-2w-0EH7iXU00OKGfUzv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "Came here on a recommendation and wasn't disappointed. We went for a half chicken with the side of fried yucca and fried rice and an order of lomo saltado. I also was told to try the chicha morada (a purple corn drink.)

Chicken was great. Since I did takeout the skin doesn't stay crisp, but the flavor was quite good. For most of the pieces, the seasoning seemed to penetrate the meat. Fried yucca is pretty much fried yucca and the fried rice was also good. I shredded up some chicken and like to mix it with the rice, yucca, plus some of the green sauce (it's got a kick!)

I barely got a taste of the lomo saltado as my wife had it. Large slices of beef. Also good flavor, more soy sauce forward and not as strong a vinegar taste.

I had no idea what to expect chicha morada, but it reminded me a lot of jamaica (hibiscus tea.)", 'time': 1660404531, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Nick S', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109115283238083063260/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu1iqIyHkD7TRmKm9JVGoNdOPObzTQvyAnk7OA24=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Since this place just opened we wanted to try as much as we could. The chicken was perfect, fries were alright but lacked flavor, and pasta salad was like what you'd buy at Giant.

Decided to get adventurous and try out the Spin Salchipapas. If you've ever had a hot dog and fries you get the idea. It was hands down one of the worst things I've ever eaten.

Everything else though, was awesome. Staff was amazing, food was great, and timely. Not sure I'd make it a regular place, but would never turn it down.", 'time': 1647204565, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Samiha I', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102502667565205222670/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu27keh7Bttt9aib9WP96yJSRM-0z-v1JT5Jp0Xb3Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "This is the newest addition to kingstowne and totally worth a trip. Spin Pollo is a local chain; I've visited their falls church location a few times. My brother and I were running some errands and he spotted it and insisted we come in. It's cute, if not a little crowded inside and the staff are very friendly. They have a decently sized menu with lots of side options. My brother and I decided to split a half chicken with two sides between us.

The portion sizes are very generous. We ordered mac and cheese and cole slaw and finished neither of them, which is saying something because my brother can EAT. Both are run of the mill, but good nonetheless. The chicken was hot and fresh and so juicy and flavorful. Some might feel it's undercooked, but it's no more undercooked than Costco rotisserie chicken (aka definitely cooked through). It comes with three sauces and all three are delicious. I'm excited to try their lomo sub next time, it looks great.", 'time': 1656290558, 'translated': False}]

name: Chopt Creative Salad Company
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Hilda Kroll', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100441671474418921617/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3KGRjm1HlFubHchXb-qe4Am5wpKuzTMu0W_djM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "A nice, clean place to stop off for a quick salad while shopping.  All the ingredients in The Orchard Salad were things I like, so I didn't have to waste time making up my mind.  Very nice staff.", 'time': 1646264905, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Kelly Johnson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112029683052548016199/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_Z7Sg_ettWtJ1EFMDYXWm7TSTdAC4hBDgN28cgOA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'I visited this restaurant several times back in December while I was staying close by for an out of town visit.  Each visit was on point in every way possible.  Fast forward six months and it's not the same restaurant.

Once again I'm visiting from out of town.  Today I stopped in for a shrimp & spinach salad.

Customer service ZERO stars.  The employee was inconvenienced by my presence, the atmosphere was awkward, uncomfortable, and un-inviting.  The restaurant was "out of shrimp and out of spinach!"  Since I don't eat chicken this left me with zero protein options, unless I opted for half a dozen eggs.  I repeated most of my order two to three times- the employee was not interested or paying attention whatsoever.  The price of bread served couldn't have been more stale.  It was the end piece and brick hard.  I don't think a stray dog would have eaten it.

I was actually embarrassed for the employee and restaurant- the fact they're "operating" under such subpar standards; unable to perform even the most basic tasks of a hospitality establishment such as inventory management, customer service, and food quality says a lot about the overall establishment and management (or lack there of).

With so many stellar restaurants to choose from in the area I don't recommend Chopt and definitely will not be back.

Please don't reply asking me to email CHOPT customer service at dot com.  I've already wasted enough time dealing with a salad restaurant being out of spinach!!!....serving a piece of brick as bread, dealing with Wednesday Adams Family customer service and writing a review to warn others.  I am not spending more time emailing customer service.  Next time I'll visit a restaurant who takes pride in their food AND service.', 'time': 1652650444, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Michael Anderson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101994685411159084786/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8siePGJTTxCjjh2bvF4kk2wqJBcd_MvwQstIgk8A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "Don't get more wrong. Their food is good and I like it. But there are two details or lack there that I just catch get pass. The first is the that quality of the food isn't what it was before the pandemic. It all seems wilted to me. The second is that a little sauce versus a lot of sauce seems hard for them to decipher. I do not like my salad drenched in sauce. But the food is good when they do it right.", 'time': 1662142452, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Sean Crook', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103346156088783377774/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-8gIEjfkdS_znlJBQq4BfzdgZlxQw1xf9AUP-F0j0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "Finally, an actual healthy addition to Kingstowne. As a new store, there's a learning curve and growing pains currently. Hopefully they can start operating more efficiently by having orders ready on time. It's nice that it opens at 10:30am for all those breakfast salad eaters out there.

I got the Cholula Chicken Salad special with jalapeño yogurt dressing and the spiciness of it worked well with the cool and crisp greens.

However, opening big plastic bags full of wet chicken and other mysterious ingredients, and disposing of the refuse right at the register was unappetizing for customers to see. Otherwise, Chop't provides ample seating and even accessible wall outlets at tables!", 'time': 1641154536, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Bros Wtf', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117669207533086237873/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu1-IAVlPzBaXR1593EwrGOR7wzwsD1mZWJ9N1G3=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Been coming here pretty consistently since it first opened. I really enjoy making my own warm grain bowl but what is extremely frustrating is that they keep changing how many toppings you can put on. When it first opened I believe it was 3 then sometime later it was 4 and then today they said I can only add 3 toppings. I’m not sure what the policy is for Chopt as to how many toppings are included but this location seems to go back and forth. Also there is always a bad smell like when you first walk in the door. Anyway, will not be returning. And please don’t ask me to email just fix the problems people have been pointing out.', 'time': 1656187031, 'translated': False}]
